%body
  %article
    %h1.title HighTables

    %p.summary
      HighTables makes it trivial to render charts from existing HTML tables using
      <a href="http://jquery.com/">jQuery</a> and
      <a href="http://www.highcharts.com/">Highcharts</a>.

    %ul.table-of-contents
      %li <a href="#line-charts">Line & Area Charts</a>
      %li <a href="#bar-charts">Bar & Column Charts</a>
      %li <a href="#pie-charts">Pie Charts</a>
      %li <a href="#installation">Installation</a>
      %li <a href="#api">API</a>

    %section#line-charts
      %h1 Line & Area Charts

      %p
        Rendering a line chart simply requires adding the <code>render-to-line-chart</code> class to
        an existing <Code>&lt;table&gt;</code> element. By default, the first column will be used to
        label the X-axis of the chart, and each column after that will be represented as a data
        series.

